name: An allem sind die Juden schuld
comments: Annemarie Hase had premiered the song in September, 1931, as a part of the political/satirical revue "Spuk in der Villa Stern" at Hollaender's legendary Berlin cabaret theatre Tingel-Tangel. As a result of the revue's great success, Electrola made a recording with the original interpreter Annemarie Hase and made test pressings. However, the record never saw release, possibly because Electrola cut back on production in the wake of the economic crisis. A few copies survived so that the recording could be released on CD decades later.
